Card to Host interrupt toggle status. HW sets corresponding interrupt toggle status to 1 whenever there is any change in INTR Status ( Posedge or Negedge ) from DUT

ERROR: Interrupt for system error scenario. 
These are not related to any particular transaction.
 SW to read INTR_ERROR_STATUS_REG�to decode type of error.�
Note: NOTE : The only way to clear ERROR field is to issue SRST of CONFIG_REG.

Description:
ERR_2 : This bit indicates a Decode error on the S-AXI interface.
 In case SW tries to access an address which is not implemented in POSH HW Bridge,
 decode error will be updated in this bit. No AXI decode error will be generated 
to avoid system level PCie error.�
0 : No error
1 : Error

ERR_1 :Error at XDMA slave interface  (this error is only valid for mode-1)

0 : No error

1 : Error

ERR_0:   Error from ACE interface.

0 : No error

1 : Error
Writing a 1 to this bits clears the respective bit in the INTR_ERROR_STATUS_REG.

EN_ERR_2 : 

1 = enables interrupt generation if  ERR_2 bit in INTR_ERROR_STATUS_REG s set
0 = disables interrupt generation

EN_ERR_1 : 

1 = enables interrupt generation if  ERR_1 bit in INTR_ERROR_STATUS_REG s set
0 = disables interrupt generation

EN_ERR_0 : 

1 = enables interrupt generation if  ERR_0 bit in INTR_ERROR_STATUS_REG s set
0 = disables interrupt generation

DESC: SW to write in corresponding Bit to set avail descritor to HW. Read to this register will always return 0.

Reading to this register will pop out one descriptor from FIFO. The popped out descriptor is returned as the read value of this register.
Depth of the fifo is MAX_DESC.
If SW reads an empty fifo, valid bit is 0. Otherwise 1.
The descriptor index popped out from the FIFO.
Number of elements present in FIFO at time of reading register.

Reading to this register will push one descriptor to FIFO.  Read to this register will always return 0.

SW must write '1' to this register. Otherwise descriptor will not be pushed into FIFO.
The descriptor index to be pushed to the FIFO.
Free space in FIFO at time of reading register.
Each bit represents completion. eg. bit 0 for completion is for descriptor 0.
Writing a 1 to this bits clears the respective bit in the intrrupt comp status register. Read to this register will always return 0.
